&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The Rubrik corporate legal team is looking for an energetic and talented Corporate Counsel with a passion for working on corporate securities, transactions and compliance matters and driving business in a fast-paced in-house environment. This position reports to Rubrik’s Senior Director, Corporate Legal and is located in Rubrik’s HQ (Palo Alto). You will work 3 days a week in the office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ul1&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li4&quot;&gt;Prepare and review SEC filings, such as Forms 10-K, 10-Q, 8-K, proxy statements, registration statements, and Section 16 reporting, including Forms 3, 4, and 5.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li4&quot;&gt;Advise on compliance with public company rules and regulations, including the Securities Act of 1933, the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, stock exchange listing standards, and Delaware law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li4&quot;&gt;Assist with corporate governance matters, including board and committee materials and meetings and governance for Rubrik’s international subsidiaries.&lt;/li&gt;
