&lt;div id=&quot;model-response-message-contentr_94cc2b54076ac6c6&quot; class=&quot;markdown markdown-main-panel enable-luminous-fast-follows enable-updated-hr-color tutor-markdown-rendering&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Rubrik has partnered with the world’s leading Global Systems Integrators (GSIs) to develop successful, profitable outcomes for our joint customers and our respective companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;17&quot;&gt;Director, GSI&lt;/strong&gt; to serve as a high-impact, strategic Individual Contributor. In this principal-level role, you will be responsible for managing, scaling, and driving unprecedented growth with select Global Systems Integrators. As a senior executive-level partner manager, you will bring a masterful track record of managing Global GSI partnerships, with a deep focus on business development, enablement, complex cost models, financial selling, and high-stakes business negotiations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success building and scaling a &lt;strong&gt;global&lt;/strong&gt; partnership with the named GSI, with deep expertise across their Managed Service Provider (MSP) business units worldwide — including a track record of co-selling, joint pipeline development, and revenue growth across multiple theatres.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to own, cultivate, and navigate C-suite and global executive relationships, driving alignment on long-term strategic goals and mutual growth priorities at the highest levels of both organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in structuring and leading &lt;strong&gt;global&lt;/strong&gt; Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs) that track performance metrics, pipeline health, forecast accuracy, and strategic alignment across regions and business units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in driving the &lt;strong&gt;global&lt;/strong&gt; design, adoption, and commercialization of embedded solutions and integrated service offerings within the GSI&#39;s broader portfolio and go-to-market motion, across all theatres.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to establish high-value executive engagement from day one at a global level — leveraging existing relationships and credibility to accelerate time-to-impact across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary global business development driver for new logo acquisition and pipeline generation — acting as the central conduit between Rubrik&#39;s global field sales organization and the GSI&#39;s worldwide partner ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to accelerate partner adoption of Rubrik&#39;s product solutions at scale, translating global technical enablement into pipeline velocity and bookings growth across multiple regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at articulating and presenting the combined Rubrik and GSI value proposition to global stakeholders, executive leadership, and customers, including at global executive briefings and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exemplary relationship management skills, with a consistent ability to build lasting, mutually valuable partnerships across GSI global leadership, Rubrik&#39;s regional field sales teams, and channel leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in identifying the GSI&#39;s global top accounts and high-potential customers, executing structured interlocks with Rubrik&#39;s regional sales organizations for opportunity registration and co-sell alignment worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of the GSI&#39;s global sales processes and deal mechanics, including path-to-contract workflows across regions, enabling accurate global forecasting and disciplined pipeline management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
